TITLE: ISIS-linked militants are threatening huge natural gas reserves the world needs badly right now
SUMMARY: Asmani Dadi had heard rumors about the insurgents. Then, one day, they came true.

TITLE: North Korea says missile tests are practice for 'tactical nuclear strikes' on South Korea
SUMMARY: North Korean state media has broken its silence over the country's recent spate of missile tests, claiming they were part of a series of simulated procedures intended to demonstrate its readiness to fire tactical nuclear warheads at potential targets in South Korea.

TITLE: Funeral rites begin for victims of mass shooting and stabbing at Thailand nursery
SUMMARY: Buddhist funeral rites have begun in the grieving town of Uthai Sawan in northern Thailand, where families are mourning the loss of children killed in a massacre at a day care center.

TITLE: Facing risk of blackouts this winter, the UK will drill for more oil in the North Sea
SUMMARY: The UK government could award oil and gas companies more than 100 new licenses to drill in the North Sea, as it looks for ways to bolster energy security amid a global supply crunch.

TITLE: Opinion: The Fed doesn't have a choice anymore. Get ready for a recession
SUMMARY: To many economists and analysts, the US economy has represented a paradox this year. On the one hand, GDP growth has slowed significantly, and some argue, even entered a recession. On the other hand, overall employment growth has been much stronger than normal.

TITLE: OPEC's production cut is a win for oil stocks
SUMMARY: The White House isn't very happy with OPEC's decision to slash oil production by 2 million barrels per day. Consumers won't be big fans either, as the move will likely send gas prices higher.

TITLE: Toyota finally figured out why wheels were falling off its electric SUV
SUMMARY: Last June, Toyota warned owners of its first mainsteam electric vehicle, the BZ4X, to stop driving their SUVs and have them transported to dealers because of a scary problem: the wheels could fall off after driving even just a few miles.

TITLE: Not only is Lake Powell's water level plummeting because of drought, its total capacity is shrinking, too
SUMMARY: Lake Powell, the second-largest human-made reservoir in the US, has lost nearly 7% of its potential storage capacity since 1963, when Glen Canyon Dam was built, a new report shows.

TITLE: These were the best and worst places for air quality in 2021, new report shows

TITLE: Big-box stores could help slash emissions and save millions by putting solar panels on roofs. Why aren't more of them doing it?

TITLE: Bella Hadid's spray-on dress goes viral at Paris Fashion Week

In much of the northern hemisphere, the busy summer season was beset by delays and cancellations, while in the United States a new study this week found that airplane passenger satisfaction is declining across the board.
